Place is known for both skylarks, Tree Pipits, Stonechats, Redstarts. It really is a gem of a place.

recordings.rmk: Bird migrating along forest edge bordering extensive farmed vineyards. Part of a migrating flock of 5 Great Tits flying low from bush to bush. Distinctive call. Great tit song in background from different birds to the ones calling. There was a major invasion of Great Tits with this type of call to Germany in winter 2012/2013. The day of the recording  was one of the first warm and sunny days in spring with remarkable passerine migration. At least 15 Great tits with this type of call moving north east were noted on this occasion within 5 hours. Equipment: Telinga Pro 7 Stereo Dat Mic, Sound Devices 702
